# AnimalScroller Privacy Policy

**Last updated: July 6, 2026**

---

## Overview

AnimalScroller is an animal photo browsing app for iPhone and iPad. This policy explains what information the app uses, how it is handled, and what is never collected.

The short version: AnimalScroller does not collect, store, or share any personal information about you. Ever.

---

## Information the app uses

### Preferences stored on your device

AnimalScroller saves two settings locally on your device using Apple's standard UserDefaults system:

- **Photo interval** — how many seconds between photos
- **Enabled categories** — which animal categories you have selected

These preferences never leave your device. They are not transmitted to any server, including ours.

### Cached photos

When you browse photos, AnimalScroller stores downloaded images in your device's local cache (up to 1 GB). This allows previously viewed photos to load without an internet connection. The cache is managed entirely by iOS and can be cleared at any time in **Settings → General → iPhone/iPad Storage → AnimalScroller → Offload App**.

---

## Third-party services

AnimalScroller fetches animal photos and article data from **Wikipedia** (operated by the Wikimedia Foundation). Each request includes a standard HTTP User-Agent header identifying the app:

```
AnimalScroller/1.0 (iOS; animal photo viewer; zpropheter@hotmail.com)
```

This header is required by Wikimedia's API policy so they can contact the developer if the app causes problems. It identifies the app and developer — not you.

Wikipedia's own privacy policy governs how Wikimedia handles these requests:
[https://foundation.wikimedia.org/wiki/Privacy_policy](https://foundation.wikimedia.org/wiki/Privacy_policy)

AnimalScroller has no other third-party integrations. There are no analytics SDKs, no advertising networks, no crash reporters, and no social logins.

---

## What we do not collect

- No name, email address, or account information
- No device identifiers (IDFA, IDFV, or similar)
- No location data
- No usage analytics or behavioral tracking
- No camera or microphone access
- No contacts or photos from your photo library
- No health or financial data

---

## Network access

AnimalScroller requests network access solely to:

1. Fetch animal photo URLs from the Wikipedia REST API
2. Download the corresponding images

No data about you or your usage is included in these requests.

The app uses Apple's Network framework (`NWPathMonitor`) to detect whether a connection is available before attempting background image enrichment. This check is performed entirely on-device and does not transmit any data.

---

## Children's privacy

AnimalScroller does not knowingly collect information from anyone, including children under 13. No account creation or personal information is required to use the app.

---

## Data retention

Because AnimalScroller collects no personal data, there is nothing to retain or delete. Your locally stored preferences and cached images can be removed at any time by deleting the app.

